Let $h$ be the length of the altitude from $A$ to $BC.$  Then $AD = \frac{2}{3} h,$ so
\[\left| \frac{BC}{2AD} \right| = \frac{3BC}{4h}.\]By the Law of Cosines,
\[h^2 = a^2 - \frac{b^2 + c^2}{2} = \frac{2a^2 - b^2 - c^2}{2} = \frac{2(BC^2 - a^2) - b^2 - c^2}{4},\]so
\[\frac{3BC}{4h} = \frac{3BC}{\sqrt{2(BC^2 - a^2) - b^2 - c^2}}.\]By the Law of Cosines again,
\[a^2 = b^2 + c^2 - 2bc \cos A.\]Then
\begin{align*}
2(BC^2 - a^2) - b^2 - c^2 &= 2(BC^2 - b^2 - c^2 + 2bc \cos A) - b^2 - c^2 \\
&= BC^2 - b^2 - c^2 + 4bc \cos A \\
&= BC^2 + 2bc \cos A - (b^2 + c^2 - 2bc \cos A) \\
&= BC^2 + 2bc \cos A - a^2.
\end{align*}Hence,
\[\frac{3BC}{\sqrt{2(BC^2 - a^2) - b^2 - c^2}} = \frac{3BC}{\sqrt{3BC^2 + 2bc \cos A - a^2}}.\]Finally,
\[a^2 = b^2 + c^2 - 2bc \cos A = b^2 + c^2 - 2bc \cos (180^\circ - B - C) = b^2 + c^2 + 2bc \cos (B + C),\]so
\[\frac{3BC}{\sqrt{3BC^2 + 2bc \cos A - a^2}} = \frac{3BC}{\sqrt{4BC^2 - 2b^2 c^2 (1 - \cos^2 A) - (b^2 + c^2)^2}} = \frac{3BC}{\sqrt{4BC^2 - (b^2 + c^2)^2 - 2b^2 c^2 \sin^2 A}}.\]We can compute $\sin A$ as follows:
\[\sin A = \sqrt{1 - \cos^2 A} = \sqrt{1 - \frac{AD^2}{AB^2}} = \sqrt{1 - \frac{4}{9}} = \frac{\sqrt{5}}{3}.\]Hence,
\begin{align*}
\frac{3BC}{\sqrt{4BC^2 - (b^2 + c^2)^2 - 2b^2 c^2 \sin^2 A}} &= \frac{3BC}{\sqrt{4BC^2 - (b^2 + c^2)^2 - \frac{10}{9} b^2 c^2}} \\
&= \frac{3BC}{\sqrt{4BC^2 - \frac{19}{9} b^2 c^2}} \\
&= \frac{3BC}{\sqrt{\frac{7}{9} BC^2 + \frac{2}{9} (BC^2 - b^2 - c^2)}} \\
&= \frac{3BC}{\sqrt{\frac{7}{9} BC^2 + \frac{8}{9} bc \cos A}} \\
&= \frac{3BC}{\sqrt{\frac{7}{9} BC^2 + \frac{8}{9} \cdot \frac{a^2 - b^2 - c^2}{2}}} \\
&= \frac{3BC}{\sqrt{\frac{7}{9} BC^2 + \frac{8}{9} \cdot \frac{(b^2 + c^2) - a^2}{2}}} \\
&= \frac{3BC}{\sqrt{\frac{7}{9} BC^2 + \frac{8}{9} \cdot \frac{(a^2 - BC^2) - 2bc \cos A}{2}}} \\
&= \frac{3BC}{\sqrt{\frac{7}{9} BC^2 + \frac{4}{9} (a^2 - BC^2) - \frac{8}{9} bc \cos A}} \\
&= \frac{3BC}{\sqrt{\frac{11}{9} BC^2 + \frac{4}{9} a^2 - \frac{8}{9} bc \cos A}}.
\end{align*}By the Law of Cosines,
\[a^2 = b^2 + c^2 - 2bc \cos A = b^2 + c^2 + 2bc \cos B \cos C.\]Then
