\[\frac{3BC}{\sqrt{\frac{11}{9} BC^2 + \frac{4}{9} (b^2 + c^2) - \frac{8}{9} bc (\cos B \cos C + \frac{1}{2})}} = \frac{3BC}{\sqrt{\frac{11}{9} BC^2 + \frac{8}{9} bc - \frac{4}{9} bc \cos A}} = \frac{3BC}{\sqrt{\frac{11}{9} BC^2 + \frac{8}{9} bc - \frac{8}{9} bc \cos B \cos C}}.\]This expression simplifies to $\boxed{3}.$

