By the Law of Cosines on triangle $ABD,$
\[\cos B = \frac{AD^2 - BD^2}{AD^2 + BD^2} = \frac{2 AD^2 - BC^2}{2 AD^2}.\]Similarly,
\[\cos C = \frac{2 AD^2 - BC^2}{2 AD^2}.\]Therefore,
\begin{align*}
\cot B - \cot C &= \frac{\cos B \sin C - \cos C \sin B}{\sin B \sin C} \\
&= \frac{\frac{2 AD^2 - BC^2}{2 AD^2} \cdot \frac{MD}{AD} - \frac{2 AD^2 - BC^2}{2 AD^2} \cdot \frac{MD}{AD}}{\frac{MD}{AD} \cdot \frac{BC}{AD}} \\
&= \frac{BC^2 - 2 AD \cdot MD}{2 AD \cdot MD} \\
&= \frac{BC^2 - AD^2}{2 AD \cdot MD} \\
&= \frac{BC^2 - AD^2}{BC \cdot MD} \\
&= \frac{BC + AD}{BC - AD}.
\end{align*}In right triangle $ABD,$ $\tan B = \frac{AD}{BD} = \frac{AD}{CD},$ so
\[\cot B = \frac{CD}{AD}.\]Then
\[\frac{BC + AD}{BC - AD} = \frac{BC/AD + 1}{BC/AD - 1} = \frac{\cot B + 1}{\cot B - 1} = \frac{CD/AD + 1}{CD/AD - 1}.\]By the Law of Cosines on triangle $ACD,$
\begin{align*}
CD^2 &= AD^2 + AC^2 - 2 AD \cdot AC \cos \angle CAD \\
&= AD^2 + \frac{BC^2}{4} - 2 AD \cdot \frac{BC}{\sqrt{4 AD^2 + BC^2}} \cdot \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} \\
&= AD^2 + \frac{BC^2}{4} - \frac{BC AD}{\sqrt{4 AD^2 + BC^2}}.
\end{align*}Then
\[\frac{CD}{AD} = \sqrt{1 + \frac{BC^2}{4 AD^2}} - \frac{BC}{2 AD},\]so
\[\frac{CD/AD + 1}{CD/AD - 1} = \frac{\sqrt{1 + \frac{BC^2}{4 AD^2}} - \frac{BC}{2 AD} + 1}{\sqrt{1 + \frac{BC^2}{4 AD^2}} - \frac{BC}{2 AD} - 1}.\]We have that
\[1 + \frac{BC^2}{4 AD^2} = 1 + \frac{BC^2}{4 MD^2} = \frac{BC^2 + 4 MD^2}{4 MD^2} = \frac{BC^2}{4 MD^2} + 1,\]so
\[\frac{\sqrt{1 + \frac{BC^2}{4 AD^2}} - \frac{BC}{2 AD} + 1}{\sqrt{1 + \frac{BC^2}{4 AD^2}} - \frac{BC}{2 AD} - 1} = \frac{\sqrt{\frac{BC^2}{4 MD^2} + 1} - \frac{BC}{2 MD} + 1}{\sqrt{\frac{BC^2}{4 MD^2} + 1} - \frac{BC}{2 MD} - 1}.\]Finally, since triangle $ABM$ is a $30^\circ$-$60^\circ$-$90^\circ$ triangle, $MD = \frac{1}{2} BC \cdot \sqrt{3},$ so
\[\frac{\sqrt{\frac{BC^2}{4 MD^2} + 1} - \frac{BC}{2 MD} + 1}{\sqrt{\frac{BC^2}{4 MD^2} + 1} - \frac{BC}{2 MD} - 1} = \frac{\sqrt{\frac{4}{3} + 1} - \sqrt{3} + 1}{\sqrt{\frac{4}{3} + 1} - \sqrt{3} - 1} = \frac{3 - \sqrt{3}}{1 - \sqrt{3}} = \boxed{3 + 2 \sqrt{3}}.\]

